            <h3>Intro</h3>
            <p>This is a game I programmed in November 2018. I used the <a href="https://docs.python.org/2/library/turtle.html">turtle</a> library in python. It is like a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Space_Invaders">space invaders</a> game. It only took me a week to make. My friends enjoy playing the game. 
            It is a simple program that can be run on any of tablets that has <a href="https://jupyter.org/">jupyter notebook</a>.</p>

            <h3>How to run it</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><p>copy the <a href="https://github.com/robingan7/AP-CS/blob/master/pythongame.py">code</a></p></li>
                <li><p>paste it in one of the python files in your jupyter notebook </p>
                <img src="/images/project/Python_Space_Invader/jupyter.png" alt="jupyter" /></li>
                <li>Run the code and you should see this
                <img src="/images/project/Python_Space_Invader/game_in.png" alt="game_in" /></li>
                </li>
            </ul>   
            <h3>Game Manual</h3>
            <ul>
            <li>You goal is to prevent the "invaders" from attacking your spaceship. You can kill one of them if your bullet hit one invader, and 
                you get <abbr>10</abbr> points after. 
            </li>    
            <li>When you hit one "invader", a <abbr>new one</abbr> will generate in a random place on the upper screen, and all the invaders also will 
                move faster. You goal is to get as many as points as possible.
            </li>
            <li>
                <code>&#11013;</code> <code>&#10145;</code> on keyboard are for moving the spaceship left and right. 
            </li>

            <li>
                <code>space</code> is for shooting bullets, and <code>A</code> is for shooting super bullets. 
            </li>

            <li>Super bullet is bigger and can hit targets easier. You get one every <abbr>30</abbr> points you score.</li>

            </ul>
